    "recap_headline": "University of Washington",
    "recap_text": "SEATTLE \u2013\nThe Huskies earned their third victory in a row on Tuesday, taking down cross-town foe Seattle U 7-4 at Husky Ballpark. Washington moves to 6-10 on the season with the win.\nThe Diamond Dawgs used a balanced and consistent offense and strong pitching to secure the win, collecting 13 hits and 15 strikeouts.\nJackson Hotchkiss\npaced the bats with four hits in four at bats, including two RBIs and two runs scored.\nJaxson Gore\nmade the start for the Huskies, going 2.1 innings with two hits and two runs allowed along with five punchouts.\nLiam Lierman\ntook over midway through the third and tossed three frames with two runs allowed and three strikeouts. The freshman earned his first career win as a result.\nPeysen Sweeney\n,\nJack Wade\n, and\nTommy Brandenburg\nthrew the final 3.2 innings, allowing only two hits and zero runs. Brandenburg earned his second save of the season in the win while Sweeney made his season debut.\nSam DeCarlo\nand\nLandon Young\neach had two hits in the game as all but one starter recorded at least one hit.\nWashington will look to keep the momentum going over the weekend as the Huskies host Ohio State for a three-game series beginning on Friday evening.\nDAWG BITES\nJackson Hotchkiss\nwent 4-4 from the plate on Tuesday, leading the Huskies to a victory\nHotchkiss has now hit safely in all four games he's played in this season\nThree Huskies are on a four-game or better hitting streak (Taggart \u2013 5, Hotchkiss \u2013 4, Bower \u2013 4)\nTaggart and\nMic Paul\nhave also reached base safely in each of the last seven games\nJackson Hotchkiss\nleads the team in slugging percentage (.778) while\nLandon Young\nhas the team's best on base percentage (.538)\nTommy Brandenburg\nearned his second save of the season on Tuesday evening\nFor news, scores, highlights and more,\ndownload the Go Huskies app\non your mobile device. Follow @UW_Baseball\u00a0on\nInstagram\n,\nX\n,\nThreads\n, and\nFacebook\nand subscribe to\nUW Athletics on YouTube\nfor the latest on the Dawgs."
